@node "Intro" "Description"
I originally intended just to make a program which could sync the Solo's
internal clock with the current system time, but I decided that some other
handy @{"features" link "Usage" 0} could easily be added, and SoloControl was born.

SoloControl allows you to have control of your Pace 56 Solo modem, using
your Amiga.  It has the following features:

- Modify the Solo's clock
- Turn call monitoring on/off
- Switch answerphone on/off
- Set number of rings before answerphone answers
- Set number of rings before the Solo automatically switches the
  answerphone on (should it be switched off)
- Toggle power saving mode on/off
- Display detailed statistics on your last modem connection
- Display all the calls in the CallerID log
- Erase the calls in the CallerID log

Amongst other things, this makes it easily possible to @{"keep logs" link "StatsLog" 0} of your
connection statistics, and to keep your Solo's clock in @{"synchronisation" link "Clock" 0}
with your Amiga's system clock.  It should be noted that STFax can also
change some of these settings too, so watch out for conflicts.
@endnode

@node "Requirements" "System Requirements"
This program needs the following in order to work:

 - Pace 56 Solo modem
 - 68020 processor or better
 - Kickstart 2.04 or higher
@endnode

