@node "History" "Program History"
@{b}1.1@{ub} (12.6.2000)

 - The GETCALLS option now works when there are more than 20 calls in the
   log - no calls were listed in 1.0 in this case
 - "The call log is empty" message from GETCALLS is no longer shown if
   QUIET is specified
 - Added some error messages for when reading the call log fails

@{b}1.0@{ub} (5.3.2000)

 - First public release

@{b}0.9Ô@{ub} (2.3.2000)

 - Added GETCALLS and DELCALLS features to view/erase the Solo's call log
 - Dates/time are now shown in the standard AmigaDOS format
 - Added some detailed examples and rejigged the documentation
 - Added ARexx script to demonstate how SoloControl can be used to
   create connection statistics logs

@{b}0.8Ô@{ub} (28.2.2000)

 - Modified serial interfacing code (a small delay is now enforced between
   the sending of each command) which will hopefully fix any erratic
   behaviour
 - Baud rate now defaults to 115200, unless using serial.device,
   artser.device or 8n1.device, where the default remains 38400 (also
   now allows gvpser.device, which doesn't support 38400 baud)
 - Added command line option allowing the baud rate to be user specified

@{b}0.7Ô@{ub} (25.2.2000)

 - Time/date string parser was a still a bit buggy - when specifying an
   invalid time/date, it never exited with an error!
 - Improved invalid time/date error message (ripped from C:Date :)

@{b}0.6Ô@{ub} (23.2.2000)

 - Removed the debug output that I accidentally left in v0.5Ô :)

@{b}0.5Ô@{ub} (23.2.2000)

 - Improved serial interfacing code, and tweaked timeouts, to hopefully
   completely wipe out the chance of SoloControl failing to get a
   response from the Solo

@{b}0.4Ô@{ub} (21.2.2000)

 - Fixed bug in my time/date string parser (specifying custom time/dates
   should work properly now)
 - When specifying a custom time and/or date, the behaviour should now
   be identical to C:Date

@{b}0.3Ô@{ub} (19.2.2000)

 - Added some additional checks, which should hopefully stop SoloControl
   not being able to identify the Solo in some cases

@{b}0.2Ô@{ub} (18.2.2000)

 - Added GETSTATS feature
 - When displaying the current settings, the firmware version is now also
   displayed
 - Increased baud rate from 19200 to 38400

@{b}0.1Ô@{ub} (17.2.2000)

 - Initial beta release.
@endnode

